CATEGORY=Special Ability|Scarlet Corsair ~ Corsair's Feint.MOD			DESC:A Scarlet Corsair is a master of dirty fighting and trickery. A Scarlet Corsair can make a feint as a free action rather than as a move action. But once surprised by a Scarlet Corsair's feint it takes time before enemies can be surprised again. At 3rd level a Scarlet Corsair must wait 2d4 rounds before feinting again. Beginning at 7th level reflexes improve and the wait time drops to 1d4 rounds.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Scarlet Corsair ~ Sailor's Step.MOD			DESC:At 4th level a Scarlet Corsair has learned to use the chaos of a ship at sea to your benefit, taking advantage of the swaying ship and swinging rigging to remain out of reach of opponents. While aboard a ship and wearing nothing more than light armor a +2 dodge bonus to AC is gained. If caught flat-footed or otherwise denied Dexterity bonus then this bonus is lost. At 8th level, this bonus increases to +4.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Scarlet Corsair ~ Scourge of the Seas.MOD		DESC:Starting at 5th level a Scarlet Corsair can instill fear in their enemies. When using Intimidate to demoralize foes, the attempt affects all enemies within 30 feet who can see and hear you, for a number of rounds equal to your Charisma modifier (%1). This is a mind-affecting ability, and multiple uses of this ability don't stack.|CHA
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Scarlet Corsair ~ Frightening Lunge.MOD		DESC:A Scarlet Corsair's ability to run their enemies through is unnerving to those who cross swords with them. Beginning at 9th level, on a successful sneak attack, you can sacrifice 2d6 damage to render a foe shaken. A shaken character takes a -2 penalty to all attack rolls, saves, skill checks, and ability checks.



