CATEGORY=Special Ability|Stormcaster ~ Storm Spell Power.MOD			DESC:Any spell cast by the Stormcaster that has the Air, Electricity, Sonic, or Water descriptor is cast at +2 caster level.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Stormcaster ~ Thunderclap.MOD					DESC:A Stormcaster can lose any prepared spell or spell slot in order to generate a 30-foot-radius burst of sonic energy. The burst deals 1d4 points of sonic damage per level of the spell slot to all targets in the area; any creature damaged by this effect is stunned for 1 round. A Fortitude save halves this damage and negates the stun effect. You are immune to your own Thunderclap power.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Stormcaster ~ Shield of Winds.MOD				DESC:Starting at 3rd level a Stormcaster can call up high winds to cast aside the arrows of their foes. As an immediate action, %1/day, they can surround their space with an effect equal to a Wind Wall spell for 1 round.|floor(StormcasterLVL/3)
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Stormcaster ~ Eye of the Storm.MOD				DESC:Even in a storm, the winds whipping around a Stormcaster leave them unaffected. Beginning at 4th level, Stormcasters ignore penalties associated with ranged attack rolls and Listen checks due to high winds. Actions that are impossible in high winds (such as using ranged attacks in winds above 50 mph) are still impossible. At 8th level, a Stormcaster gains the ability to share this protection with any number of allies within 30 feet. Granting (or removing) this benefit from any number of allies is a free action.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Stormcaster ~ Thunderbolt.MOD					DESC:Beginning at 5th level, a Stormcaster's knowledge of the storm to add the power of thunder to their lightning-based spells. Any spell they cast that deals electricity damage also deals an extra 1 point of sonic damage per spell level and stuns any creature damaged by the spell for 1 round (Fortitude save negates; DC equals the save DC of the spell even if the spell wouldn't normally allow a save).
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Stormcaster ~ Call Storm.MOD					DESC:At 8th level, a Stormcaster gains the ability to use a Control Weather effect once per week but can only create a windstorm, thunderstorm, or hurricane-force winds. A Stormcaster is treated as a Druid when using this ability for the purpose of duration and area of the spell.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Stormcaster ~ Lord of the Storm.MOD			DESC:At 10th level, a Stormcaster's mastery of the power of the storm is complete. They gain resistance to electricity 30 and resistance to sonic 30. They are immune to being blown away, knocked down, or checked by high winds (whether natural or magical). They gain a +2 competence bonus on saves against spells with Air or Water descriptors.

	